  "original_title": "Sri Lanka to get UN\u2019s support to achieve 2030 agenda for sustainable development",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka to get UN\u2019s support to achieve 2030 agenda for sustainable development",
      "author": "Chanka Jayasinghe",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT- Sri Lanka has agreed to sign the Sustainable Development Cooperation Framework (UNSDCF) 2023- 2027 by the United Nations, in hopes of accelerating actions towards the achievement of the 2030 agenda for sustainable development, a statement from the Prime Minister\u2019s office said.",
        "The statement said during the meeting between the UN Development Coordination Office (UNDCO) Regional Director for Asia and the Pacific David McLachlan-Karr and Prime Minister Dinesh Gunawardena, the former had assured the PM that the UNDCO would extend every possible assistance to Sri Lanka\u2019s development programmes related to Sustainable Development Goals, green economy, social cohesion and social protection.",
        "This Cooperation Framework is anchored in a human rights-based approach and is underpinned by the principle of leaving no-one behind as the country makes progress on all three pillars of sustainable development \u2013 economic, social and environmental, the statement said.",
        "\u201cThe collective results expected from the Cooperation Framework will contribute to a vision where all people in Sri Lanka, especially the most vulnerable, contribute to and benefit from inclusive, just, sustainable and rights-based development in a resilient, peaceful and cohesive society, leading to the achievement of the 2030 Agenda and its SDGs,\u201d the UNSDCF document date June, 2022 said.",
        "At the centre of the Cooperation Framework is a focus on investing in people, it said.",
        "\u201cThe policy framework seeks to minimise inequality and eliminate poverty, improve people\u2019s health and lifestyle through the promotion of sustainable and nutritious agricultural practices, provide good education for all, make clean drinking water and cost-effective energy available, ensure gainful employment for youth through green industries, the greening of cities to make them suitable for human habitation, ensure equal and better opportunities for women, address issues of climate change and prevent the pollution of oceans, safeguard bio-diversity and establish a society that values and promotes peace.\u201d",
        "The Prime Minister office said that, during the discussions, Gunawardena had stressed pm the need for accelerated actions to ensure a rapid recovery from the economic crisis along with the impact of COVID-19 and on prioritising support to revitalise the economy and economic activities, social services, decent employment, social cohesion, and health and well-being for all people in Sri Lanka. (Colombo/Aug 20/2022)"
      ],
